President Obama announced his intent to appoint several individuals to the President's Advisory Council on Faith-Based and Neighborhood Partnerships. The council brings together religious and secular leaders, scholars, and experts to make recommendations to the government on improving partnerships with faith-based and neighborhood organizations. The appointed individuals include Susan K. Stern, Leith Anderson, Andrea Baz√°n, Angela Glover Blackwell, Brian Gallagher, Bishop Mark Hanson, Lynn Hybels, The Most Rev. Dr. Katharine Jefferts Schori, Rabbi Julie Schonfeld, Archbishop Demetrios Trakatellis, Sister Marlene Weisenbeck, and Reverend Elder Nancy L. Wilson. These individuals have backgrounds in various fields, such as humanitarian assistance, evangelical ministry, philanthropy, advocacy, and religious leadership.